{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1120,"text":"Interestingly, Charles Darwin"},{"time":4000,"text":"was born a very lightly pigmented man,"},{"time":8000,"text":"in a moderately-to-darkly pigmented world."},{"time":12000,"text":"Over the course of his life,"},{"time":15000,"text":"Darwin had great privilege."},{"time":17000,"text":"He lived in a fairly wealthy home."},{"time":20000,"text":"He was raised by very supportive and interested parents."},{"time":24000,"text":"And when he was in his 20s"},{"time":26000,"text":"he embarked upon a remarkable voyage \non the ship the Beagle."},{"time":30000,"text":"And during the course of that voyage,"},{"time":33000,"text":"he saw remarkable things:"},{"time":35000,"text":"tremendous diversity of plants and animals, and humans."},{"time":39000,"text":"And the observations that he made"},{"time":41000,"text":"on that epic journey"},{"time":43000,"text":"were to be eventually distilled"},{"time":45000,"text":"into his wonderful book, \"On the Origin of Species,\""},{"time":47000,"text":"published 150 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"Now what is so interesting"},{"time":53000,"text":"and to some, the extent, what's a bit infamous"},{"time":57000,"text":"about \"The Origin of Species,\""},{"time":59000,"text":"is that there is only one line in it"},{"time":61000,"text":"about human evolution."},{"time":64000,"text":"\"Light will be thrown on the origin of man"},{"time":67000,"text":"and his history.\""},{"time":69000,"text":"It wasn't until much longer,"},{"time":71000,"text":"much later,"},{"time":73000,"text":"that Darwin actually spoke"},{"time":75000,"text":"and wrote about humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78000,"text":"Now in his years of"},{"time":80000,"text":"traveling on the Beagle,"},{"time":82000,"text":"and from listening to the accounts"},{"time":84000,"text":"or explorers and naturalists,"},{"time":86000,"text":"he knew that skin color"},{"time":90000,"text":"was one of the most important ways"},{"time":92000,"text":"in which people varied."},{"time":94000,"text":"And he was somewhat interested in the pattern of skin color."},{"time":98000,"text":"He knew that darkly pigmented peoples"},{"time":100000,"text":"were found close to the equator;"},{"time":103000,"text":"lightly pigmented peoples, like himself,"},{"time":105000,"text":"were found closer to the poles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"So what did he make of all this?"},{"time":110000,"text":"Well he didn't write anything about it in The Origin of Species."},{"time":113000,"text":"But much later, in 1871,"},{"time":116000,"text":"he did have something to say about it."},{"time":118000,"text":"And it was quite curious. He said,"},{"time":120000,"text":"\"Of all the differences between the races of men,"},{"time":123000,"text":"the color of the skin is the most conspicuous"},{"time":125000,"text":"and one of the best marked.\""},{"time":127000,"text":"And he went on to say,"},{"time":129000,"text":"\"These differences do not coincide"},{"time":132000,"text":"with corresponding differences in climate.\""},{"time":135000,"text":"So he had traveled all around."},{"time":137000,"text":"He had seen people of different colors"},{"time":140000,"text":"living in different places."},{"time":142000,"text":"And yet he rejected the idea"},{"time":144000,"text":"that human skin pigmentation"},{"time":147000,"text":"was related to the climate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"If only Darwin lived today."},{"time":153000,"text":"If only Darwin had NASA."},{"time":156000,"text":"Now, one of the wonderful things that NASA does"},{"time":160000,"text":"is it puts up a variety of satellites"},{"time":162000,"text":"that detect all sort of interesting things about our environment."},{"time":165000,"text":"And for many decades now"},{"time":168000,"text":"there have been a series of TOMS satellites"},{"time":171000,"text":"that have collected data about the radiation of the Earth's surface."},{"time":174000,"text":"The TOMS 7 satellite data, shown here,"},{"time":178000,"text":"show the annual average"},{"time":180000,"text":"ultraviolet radiation at the Earth's surface."},{"time":183000,"text":"Now the really hot pink and red areas"},{"time":186000,"text":"are those parts of the world that receive the highest amounts"},{"time":189000,"text":"of UV during the year."},{"time":192000,"text":"The incrementally cooler colors --"},{"time":195000,"text":"blues, greens, yellows, and finally grays --"},{"time":198000,"text":"indicate areas of much lower ultraviolet radiation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"What's significant to the story of human skin pigmentation"},{"time":205000,"text":"is just how much of the Northern Hemisphere"},{"time":209000,"text":"is in these cool gray zones."},{"time":212000,"text":"This has tremendous implications for our understanding"},{"time":215000,"text":"of the evolution of human skin pigmentation."},{"time":218000,"text":"And what Darwin could not appreciate,"},{"time":221000,"text":"or didn't perhaps want to appreciate at the time,"},{"time":224000,"text":"is that there was a fundamental relationship"},{"time":227000,"text":"between the intensity of ultraviolet radiation"},{"time":230000,"text":"and skin pigmentation."},{"time":232000,"text":"And that skin pigmentation itself"},{"time":235000,"text":"was a product of evolution."},{"time":238000,"text":"And so when we look at a map of skin color,"},{"time":241000,"text":"and predicted skin color, as we know it today,"},{"time":244000,"text":"what we see is a beautiful gradient"},{"time":247000,"text":"from the darkest skin pigmentations toward the equator,"},{"time":250000,"text":"and the lightest ones toward the poles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"What's very, very important here"},{"time":257000,"text":"is that the earliest humans"},{"time":259000,"text":"evolved in high-UV environments,"},{"time":262000,"text":"in equatorial Africa."},{"time":264000,"text":"The earliest members of our lineage,"},{"time":267000,"text":"the genus Homo, were darkly pigmented."},{"time":270000,"text":"And we all share this incredible heritage"},{"time":274000,"text":"of having originally been"},{"time":276000,"text":"darkly pigmented,"},{"time":278000,"text":"two million to one and half million years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"Now what happened in our history?"},{"time":286000,"text":"Let's first look at the relationship"},{"time":288000,"text":"of ultraviolet radiation to the Earth's surface."},{"time":291000,"text":"In those early days of our evolution,"},{"time":294000,"text":"looking at the equator,"},{"time":296000,"text":"we were bombarded by high levels of ultraviolet radiation."},{"time":299000,"text":"The UVC, the most energetic type,"},{"time":302000,"text":"was occluded by the Earth's atmosphere."},{"time":305000,"text":"But UVB and UVA"},{"time":307000,"text":"especially, came in unimpeded."},{"time":309000,"text":"UVB turns out to be incredibly important."},{"time":313000,"text":"It's very destructive,"},{"time":315000,"text":"but it also catalyzes the production of vitamin D in the skin,"},{"time":319000,"text":"vitamin D being a molecule that we very much need"},{"time":323000,"text":"for our strong bones, the health of our immune system,"},{"time":327000,"text":"and myriad other important functions in our bodies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330000,"text":"So, living at the equator, we got"},{"time":332000,"text":"lots and lots of ultraviolet radiation"},{"time":335000,"text":"and the melanin --"},{"time":338000,"text":"this wonderful, complex, ancient polymer"},{"time":342000,"text":"compound in our skin --"},{"time":344000,"text":"served as a superb natural sunscreen."},{"time":348000,"text":"This polymer is amazing"},{"time":350000,"text":"because it's present in so many different organisms."},{"time":353000,"text":"Melanin, in various forms, has probably been on the Earth"},{"time":355000,"text":"a billion years,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and has been recruited over and over again"},{"time":360000,"text":"by evolution, as often happens."},{"time":364000,"text":"Why change it if it works?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":366000,"text":"So melanin was recruited, in our lineage,"},{"time":370000,"text":"and specifically in our earliest ancestors"},{"time":373000,"text":"evolving in Africa,"},{"time":375000,"text":"to be a natural sunscreen."},{"time":377000,"text":"Where it protected the body"},{"time":379000,"text":"against the degradations of ultraviolet radiation,"},{"time":382000,"text":"the destruction, or damage to DNA,"},{"time":385000,"text":"and the breakdown of a very important molecule called folate,"},{"time":389000,"text":"which helps to fuel cell production,"},{"time":392000,"text":"and reproduction in the body."},{"time":395000,"text":"So, it's wonderful. We evolved this very protective,"},{"time":398000,"text":"wonderful covering of melanin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401000,"text":"But then we moved."},{"time":405000,"text":"And humans dispersed -- not once, but twice."},{"time":409000,"text":"Major moves, outside of our equatorial homeland,"},{"time":413000,"text":"from Africa into other parts of the Old World,"},{"time":417000,"text":"and most recently, into the New World."},{"time":419000,"text":"When humans dispersed into these latitudes,"},{"time":422000,"text":"what did they face?"},{"time":424000,"text":"Conditions were significantly colder,"},{"time":427000,"text":"but they were also less intense"},{"time":429000,"text":"with respect to the ultraviolet regime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"So if we're somewhere in the Northern Hemisphere,"},{"time":435000,"text":"look at what's happening to the ultraviolet radiation."},{"time":438000,"text":"We're still getting a dose of UVA."},{"time":441000,"text":"But all of the UVB,"},{"time":443000,"text":"or nearly all of it,"},{"time":445000,"text":"is dissipated through the thickness of the atmosphere."},{"time":448000,"text":"In the winter, when you are skiing in the Alps,"},{"time":452000,"text":"you may experience ultraviolet radiation."},{"time":455000,"text":"But it's all UVA,"},{"time":457000,"text":"and, significantly, that UVA"},{"time":459000,"text":"has no ability to make vitamin D in your skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"So people inhabiting northern hemispheric environments"},{"time":469000,"text":"were bereft of the potential"},{"time":472000,"text":"to make vitamin D in their skin for most of the year."},{"time":475000,"text":"This had tremendous consequences"},{"time":478000,"text":"for the evolution of human skin pigmentation."},{"time":480000,"text":"Because what happened, in order to ensure health and well-being,"},{"time":485000,"text":"these lineages of people"},{"time":487000,"text":"dispersing into the Northern Hemisphere"},{"time":491000,"text":"lost their pigmentation."},{"time":493000,"text":"There was natural selection"},{"time":495000,"text":"for the evolution of lightly pigmented skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500000,"text":"Here we begin to see the evolution"},{"time":502000,"text":"of the beautiful sepia rainbow"},{"time":504000,"text":"that now characterizes all of humanity."},{"time":507000,"text":"Lightly pigmented skin evolved not just once,"},{"time":511000,"text":"not just twice, but probably three times."},{"time":514000,"text":"Not just in modern humans,"},{"time":516000,"text":"but in one of our distant unrelated ancestors,"},{"time":520000,"text":"the Neanderthals."},{"time":522000,"text":"A remarkable, remarkable testament"},{"time":524000,"text":"to the power of evolution."},{"time":526000,"text":"Humans have been on the move for a long time."},{"time":529000,"text":"And just in the last 5,000 years,"},{"time":531000,"text":"in increasing rates, over increasing distances."},{"time":534000,"text":"Here are just some of the biggest movements of people,"},{"time":538000,"text":"voluntary movements, in the last 5,000 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"Look at some of the major latitudinal transgressions:"},{"time":544000,"text":"people from high UV areas"},{"time":546000,"text":"going to low UV and vice versa."},{"time":549000,"text":"And not all these moves were voluntary."},{"time":553000,"text":"Between 1520 and 1867,"},{"time":556000,"text":"12 million, 500 people"},{"time":560000,"text":"were moved from high UV"},{"time":562000,"text":"to low UV areas"},{"time":564000,"text":"in the transatlantic slave trade."},{"time":567000,"text":"Now this had all sorts of invidious social consequences."},{"time":571000,"text":"But it also had deleterious"},{"time":574000,"text":"health consequences to people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576000,"text":"So what? We've been on the move."},{"time":579000,"text":"We're so clever we can overcome all of these"},{"time":582000,"text":"seeming biological impediments."},{"time":585000,"text":"Well, often we're unaware"},{"time":587000,"text":"of the fact that we're living"},{"time":589000,"text":"in environments in which our skin"},{"time":591000,"text":"is inherently poorly adapted."},{"time":594000,"text":"Some of us with lightly pigmented skin"},{"time":596000,"text":"live in high-UV areas."},{"time":598000,"text":"Some of us with darkly pigmented skin"},{"time":600000,"text":"live in low-UV areas."},{"time":603000,"text":"These have tremendous consequences for our health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607000,"text":"We have to, if we're lightly pigmented,"},{"time":610000,"text":"be careful about the problems of skin cancer,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and destruction of folate in our bodies,"},{"time":617000,"text":"by lots of sun."},{"time":619000,"text":"Epidemiologists and doctors"},{"time":621000,"text":"have been very good about telling us"},{"time":623000,"text":"about protecting our skin."},{"time":625000,"text":"What they haven't been so good about instructing people"},{"time":630000,"text":"is the problem of darkly pigmented people"},{"time":633000,"text":"living in high latitude areas,"},{"time":636000,"text":"or working inside all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"Because the problem there is just as severe,"},{"time":641000,"text":"but it is more sinister,"},{"time":643000,"text":"because vitamin D deficiency,"},{"time":645000,"text":"from a lack of ultraviolet B radiation,"},{"time":649000,"text":"is a major problem."},{"time":651000,"text":"Vitamin D deficiency creeps up on people,"},{"time":653000,"text":"and causes all sorts of health problems to their bones,"},{"time":656000,"text":"to their gradual decay of their immune systems,"},{"time":660000,"text":"or loss of immune function,"},{"time":662000,"text":"and probably some problems"},{"time":664000,"text":"with their mood and health,"},{"time":667000,"text":"their mental health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669000,"text":"So we have, in skin pigmentation,"},{"time":672000,"text":"one of these wonderful products of evolution"},{"time":675000,"text":"that still has consequences for us today."},{"time":677000,"text":"And the social consequences,"},{"time":679000,"text":"as we know, are incredibly profound."},{"time":682000,"text":"We live in a world where we"},{"time":684000,"text":"have lightly and darkly pigmented people"},{"time":688000,"text":"living next to one another,"},{"time":690000,"text":"but often brought into proximity initially"},{"time":693000,"text":"as a result of very invidious social interactions."},{"time":697000,"text":"So how can we overcome this?"},{"time":700000,"text":"How can we begin to understand it?"},{"time":702000,"text":"Evolution helps us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706000,"text":"200 years after Darwin's birthday,"},{"time":710000,"text":"we have the first moderately pigmented President of the United States."},{"time":715000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":716000,"text":"How wonderful is that?"},{"time":718000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":720000,"text":"This man is significant for a whole host of reasons."},{"time":724000,"text":"But we need to think about how he compares,"},{"time":727000,"text":"in terms of his pigmentation, to other people on Earth."},{"time":729000,"text":"He, as one of many urban admixed populations,"},{"time":733000,"text":"is very emblematic"},{"time":735000,"text":"of a mixed parentage, of a mixed pigmentation."},{"time":738000,"text":"And he resembles, very closely,"},{"time":740000,"text":"people with moderate levels of pigmentation"},{"time":743000,"text":"who live in southern Africa, or Southeast Asia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"These people have a tremendous potential"},{"time":749000,"text":"to tan, to develop more pigment in their skin,"},{"time":752000,"text":"as a result of exposure to sun."},{"time":754000,"text":"They also run the risk of vitamin D deficiency,"},{"time":758000,"text":"if they have desk jobs, like that guy."},{"time":762000,"text":"So lets all wish for his great health,"},{"time":766000,"text":"and his awareness of his own skin pigmentation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"Now what is wonderful"},{"time":774000,"text":"about the evolution of human skin pigmentation,"},{"time":778000,"text":"and the phenomenon of pigmentation,"},{"time":780000,"text":"is that it is the demonstration,"},{"time":783000,"text":"the evidence, of evolution"},{"time":786000,"text":"by natural selection,"},{"time":788000,"text":"right on your body."},{"time":792000,"text":"When people ask you, \"What is the evidence for evolution?\""},{"time":795000,"text":"You don't have to think about some exotic examples, or fossils."},{"time":799000,"text":"You just have to look at your skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802000,"text":"Darwin, I think, would have appreciated this,"},{"time":806000,"text":"even though he eschewed the importance"},{"time":809000,"text":"of climate on the evolution of pigmentation during his own life."},{"time":813000,"text":"I think, were he able to look"},{"time":816000,"text":"at the evidence we have today, he would understand it."},{"time":819000,"text":"He would appreciate it."},{"time":821000,"text":"And most of all, he would teach it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"You, you can teach it."},{"time":828000,"text":"You can touch it."},{"time":830000,"text":"You can understand it."},{"time":832000,"text":"Take it out of this room."},{"time":835000,"text":"Take your skin color,"},{"time":837000,"text":"and celebrate it."},{"time":839000,"text":"Spread the word."},{"time":841000,"text":"You have the evolution"},{"time":843000,"text":"of the history of our species,"},{"time":847000,"text":"part of it, written in your skin."},{"time":849000,"text":"Understand it. Appreciate it. Celebrate it."},{"time":852000,"text":"Go out. Isn't it beautiful? Isn't it wonderful?"},{"time":856000,"text":"You are the products of evolution."},{"time":859000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":861000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}